✅ EXPERIMENT 1 – Familiarization
Aim

To study the architecture and programming of 8051 microcontroller using simulator.

Theory
8051 is an 8-bit microcontroller used in embedded systems
It has CPU, 128B RAM, 4KB ROM, timers, and I/O ports
It provides 4 ports (P0–P3) with 32 I/O pins
Supports interrupts and serial communication
Executes instructions stored in memory
Works on clock signal
EdSim51 is used for simulation
Simulator Used

EdSim51

Code
ORG 0000H
MOV A, #25H
MOV R0, #10H
ADD A, R0
HERE: SJMP HERE
END
Observation
A loaded with 25H, R0 with 10H
ADD executed successfully
Result A = 35H
Infinite loop observed
Registers updated correctly
Conclusion

Thus, 8051 architecture and program execution were successfully verified.
